fields.Title: WHIRLING F2 ORB / Faschist Quest Initiation
fields.Description: Endurance urges you to find a way to turn back time -- in the name of Revachol, in the name of love.

fields.Title: Endurance: "Back there, in your sleep. All the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Back there, in your sleep. All the weak-willed delinquents, dilly-dalliers, foreign moneylenders, insane anarchists, and yes -- the wöömen -- they've run this place to ruin.

fields.Title: You: "I like it just fine right here, rig..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I like it just fine right here, right now. [Discard thought.]

fields.Title: Endurance: "Protect the Suzerainty, clean up th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Protect the Suzerainty, clean up the city, revive disco music, and get her back? You could save Revachol. You could be the *man*, bröther.

fields.Title: Half Light: "Love is shit, loyalty is meaningles..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Love is shit, loyalty is meaningless.

fields.Title: You: "So how do I find these men?"
fields.Dialogue Text: So how do I find these men?

fields.Title: You: "No one comes to mind."
fields.Dialogue Text: No one comes to mind.

dialogueEntries.conditionsString: Variable["plaza.fascha_q_initiation_found_gary"] == false  and  Variable["plaza.fascha_q_initiation_found_measurehead"] == false  and  Variable["plaza.fascha_q_initiation_found_lorryman"] == false  and  Variable["plaza.fascha_q_initiation_found_rene"] == false  and  Variable["plaza.fascha_q_initiation_suggested_paledriver"] == false

fields.Title: Endurance: "Yeah, that was a good one -- a trea..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yeah, that was a good one -- a treasure trove of wisdom -- but don't worry, there must be *others*.

fields.Title: Logic: "Three 'traditionalists' should be e..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Three 'traditionalists' should be enough. No need to overdo it.

fields.Title: Jump to: [Endurance: "There must be others like you. Men,..."]
Endurance: "No, not her. She's a woman. Anyone..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No, not her. She's a woman. Anyone else?

fields.Title: Endurance: "But just imagine... to go back with..."
fields.Dialogue Text: But just imagine... to go back with the knowledge and the experience you now have and do it all over. Do it *richtig* this time?

fields.Title: You: "You know, I think I'm just gonna le..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You know, I think I'm just gonna let this one slide. [Opt out.]

fields.Title: You: "I *do* feel like everything's gone..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I *do* feel like everything's gone to shit...

fields.Title: You: "Those sons of bitches..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Those sons of bitches...

fields.Title: Endurance: "The game was rigged from before you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The game was rigged from before you even knew how the pieces move, söldier. (The tightness spreads to your gut.)

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Her?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Her?

fields.Title: You: "Okay, how do we do this?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Okay, how do we do this?

fields.Title: Endurance: "You want to give up on redemption?..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You want to give up on redemption? *Revanche?* On Revachol?! I had you for a kingsman, bröther.

fields.Title: Endurance: "Now *there* is man who values the p..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Now *there* is man who values the past with passion. And you know how the saying goes: He who clings to the past, shapes the future.

fields.Title: Endurance: "That's a good number of traditional..."
fields.Dialogue Text: That's a good number of traditionalists. It's *ample*. Let's go see what they know.

fields.Title: Endurance: "Don't be ridiculous. They are all m..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Don't be ridiculous. They are all men, trust me.

fields.Title: Endurance: "Now we're making bank! A man with *..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Now we're making bank! A man with *guts* and a *memory*. I felt it too. He could be a treasure trove of wisdom. Who else?

fields.Title: Endurance: "They're still all men, of course."
fields.Dialogue Text: They're still all men, of course.

fields.Title: You: "What's going on with my gut, did I..."
fields.Dialogue Text: What's going on with my gut, did I not *eat* enough?

fields.Title: Endurance: "To go back with the knowledge and t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: To go back with the knowledge and the experience you have now and do it all over? Do it *richtig* this time?

fields.Title: You: "Wait, get who back?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Wait, get who back?

fields.Title: Endurance: "There must be others like you. Men,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There must be others like you. Men, who long for the days when words like 'loyalty' and 'love' meant something.

fields.Title: Endurance: "Think. Maybe you've already met som..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Think. Maybe you've already met someone like that?

fields.Title: You: "Gary would probably appreciate Old..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Gary would probably appreciate Old Revachol.

fields.Title: Endurance: "Four is a good number of traditiona..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Four is a good number of traditionalists. It's *plenty*. Let's go see what they know.

fields.Title: Endurance: "No, bröther, forget about your gut,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No, bröther, forget about your gut, we've got much more pressing matters to focus on. It’s time to *turn back time*. (A solemn gurgle emanates from the depths of your stomach.)

fields.Title: You: "Wait, one of them could easily be a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Wait, one of them could easily be a woman.

fields.Title: You: "I got a feeling Measurehead fits th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I got a feeling Measurehead fits that description.
fields.Alternate1: Measurehead seemed to long for the glory days of his Semenese ancestors...

fields.Title: Endurance: "Okay, don't worry -- that's what yo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Okay, don't worry -- that's what your gut is for, *feeling* these things out. Let me be your eyes and when I know for sure someone's got that special *something*, I'll tip you off.

fields.Title: You: "Yeah... I think I'm gonna let this..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yeah... I think I'm gonna let this one slide.

fields.Title: Endurance: "People whose yearning for the past..."
fields.Dialogue Text: People whose yearning for the past is so great they barely live in the present. Those are the men you need to find. Those are the guys who'd know.

fields.Title: You: "You had me wrong. [Opt out.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: You had me wrong. [Opt out.]

fields.Title: You: "No one else comes to mind."
fields.Dialogue Text: No one else comes to mind.

fields.Title: Endurance: "You were right, bröther. (There's a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You were right, bröther. (There's a sudden tightness in your lower intestine.)

fields.Title: You: "I'm not sure if I'm *feeling it*."
fields.Dialogue Text: I'm not sure if I'm *feeling it*.

fields.Title: You: "What? What's going on?"
fields.Dialogue Text: What? What's going on?

fields.Title: Shivers: "A chill runs down your spine when y..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A chill runs down your spine when you hear the name of your light -- Revachol...

fields.Title: You: "That grey-haired lorry driver might..."
fields.Dialogue Text: That grey-haired lorry driver might know something.

fields.Title: Logic: "Three to four 'traditionalists' sho..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Three to four 'traditionalists' should do it. No need to go crazy with those guys.

fields.Title: Endurance: "But you did. Not with words, but yo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: But you did. Not with words, but you *did*, bröther. (The tightness spreads to your gut.)

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "That is *not* a saying. It makes no..."
fields.Dialogue Text: That is *not* a saying. It makes no sense.

fields.Title: You: "Even if it was possible, what would..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Even if it was possible, what would it accomplish?

fields.Title: Volition: "No one, don't ask about her."
fields.Dialogue Text: No one, don't ask about her.

fields.Title: Endurance: "Second chances are not about questi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Second chances are not about questions, they are about actions. Are you ready to start taking action, bröther?

fields.Title: Endurance: "Oh yes. (Your lower intestine rumbl..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Oh yes. (Your lower intestine rumbles approvingly.) Gary is *exactly* the kind of guy we want. He knows something! Who else?

fields.Title: Endurance: "Bullseye! (A reassuring rumble in y..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Bullseye! (A reassuring rumble in your guts.) And *that's* the vibe we're looking for. *Those* are the people with answers.

fields.Title: You: "Think of all the possibilities... I..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Think of all the possibilities... I want this.

fields.Title: Volition: "You fool!"
fields.Dialogue Text: You fool!

fields.Title: Endurance: "I will send you back to the time wh..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I will send you back to the time when the sun had not yet vanished, when it was still setting into the sea. The time of the Suzerain, the time when love was still possible.

fields.Title: You: "Wait, couldn't one of them be a gir..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Wait, couldn't one of them be a girl?

fields.Title: Endurance: "History will remember us, and this..."
fields.Dialogue Text: History will remember us, and this time we don't have to worry about her being kind. *Praeterita redire*, kingsman. Charge for Revachol, charge for *love*!

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "And by 'longing' you meant 'blatant..."
fields.Dialogue Text: And by 'longing' you meant 'blatantly racist', right?

fields.Title: Endurance: "It has, bröther, but we are going t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It has, bröther, but we are going to turn back time! (A solemn gurgle emanates from your stomach.)

fields.Title: You: "Well, if it's for Revachol... (Cont..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Well, if it's for Revachol... (Continue.)

fields.Title: You: "The fat lorryman was giving off tha..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The fat lorryman was giving off that longing vibe.

fields.Title: You: "I didn't actually say that."
fields.Dialogue Text: I didn't actually say that.

fields.Title: Endurance: "Measurehead is *exactly* the kind o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Measurehead is *exactly* the kind of man who'd know how to step back into the past.

fields.Title: Volition: "Ultramarathon here meant Revachol...."
fields.Dialogue Text: Ultramarathon here meant Revachol. Our streets and all that. It's all there is. Just move on and answer the question.

fields.Title: You: "No one misses the good old days lik..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No one misses the good old days like René.

dialogueEntries.conditionsString: Variable["plaza.rene_know_dead"] == false  and  Variable["plaza.rene_finished_crater_branch"] == true  and  Variable["plaza.fascha_q_initiation_found_rene"] == false

fields.Title: You: "René really missed the good old day..."
fields.Dialogue Text: René really missed the good old days. Too bad he's dead.
fields.Alternate1: René really missed the good old days. Too bad he's dead. (Run your fingers over the medal on your chest.)
fields.Alternate2: René really missed the good old days. Too bad he's dead. (Straighten your back in the uniform -- it demands it.)
fields.Alternate3: René really missed the good old days. Too bad he's dead. (Glance at your jacket.)
fields.Alternate4: René really missed the good old days. Too bad he's dead. (Mournfully slap the side of your striped thigh.)

dialogueEntries.conditionsString: Variable["plaza.rene_know_dead"] == true  and  Variable["plaza.rene_finished_crater_branch"] == true  and  Variable["plaza.fascha_q_initiation_endurance_too_bad_rene_dead"] == false

fields.Title: You: "Alright, I'm in. [Opt in.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: Alright, I'm in. [Opt in.]

fields.Title: Endurance: "Sure. Revachol will do just fine wi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Sure. Revachol will do just fine without you. Don't worry about her.
